<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_VARIABLE_SHADING_RATE_TIER">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines constants that specify a shading rate tier (for variable-rate shading, or VRS). For more info, see <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/vrs">Variable-rate shading (VRS)</a>.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/vrs">Variable-rate shading (VRS)</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VARIABLE_SHADING_RATE_TIER.D3D12_VARIABLE_SHADING_RATE_TIER_NOT_SUPPORTED">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies that variable-rate shading is not supported.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VARIABLE_SHADING_RATE_TIER.D3D12_VARIABLE_SHADING_RATE_TIER_1">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies that variable-rate shading tier 1 is supported.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_VARIABLE_SHADING_RATE_TIER.D3D12_VARIABLE_SHADING_RATE_TIER_2">
    <summary>
      <para>Specifies that variable-rate shading tier 2 is supported.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>